<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\b_valleymielavest\item_ancientspiritcube</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>35</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>You hold the small metal cube in the palms of your hands. It spreads warmth throughout your body. You can barely make out a soothing voice whispering softly.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Listen closely to the voice.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put your ear to the machine again.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Putting your ear closely to the cube, the words are starting to become clear, if fragmentary. "...mighty warlords, yet so small ... So you shall understand me ... your help ... not free, wisdom to bestow ... like so..."

It rapidly rattles off a series of instructions, and then starts repeating them. You're not entirely sure you could follow them, or what would happen if you do.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>The cube is repeating the instructions on how to connect its power source, but they are spoken too quickly for you to understand.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try to figure out the cube's instructions.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try again to figure out the cube's instructions.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>You can figure out most of the instructions, and once the intelligence points them out the connectors and activation methods seem obvious. But a few steps are explained in an obscure manner.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>Try as you might, you can't make sense of what the machine is saying or how it relates to its different bits and pieces.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Go back to go forward ... revolve the crux ... go forward to go back ... only now, final."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>Depress the main controller node.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>Detach the power source.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Switch the colored wiring.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>Rotate the core.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>A clanking noise reverbs and the machine angrily buzzes at you, instantly reverting to its original state.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Put the cube away.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Nothing happens.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>Reattach the power source.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>Rotate the core.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>The core rotates easily at your touch, and clicks into a new position.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>Reattach the power source.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>The cube is rapidly heating up, emitting a high pitched sound.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>Depress the main controller node.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>The cube hisses and releases some kind of energy outwards, through your arms. As it courses through your body, exploring your form somehow.

It takes you a moment to realize that as it passed, it left new, unfamiliar memories etched into your mind. These memories appear to have belonged to an ancient automaton craftsman, and they increase your understanding of all things mechanical.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>The cube itself becomes cold and deadly silent, then begins to fall apart in your hands. You scavenge some valuable bits from the object.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>Each step matches a specific part of the device. It seems you have to detach the power source to rotate the core of the device, after which you can safely reattach the power source and switch the device on.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>Inspect the device closely, seeing how the different parts fit the odd instructions.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>Follow the instructions to switch the device on.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>